The aircraft operator referred to in section 2 (2) above shall:
* monitor its emissions and tonne-kilometres, draw up an annual report on its emissions and have the report verified;
* submit the monitoring plan to the Finnish Transport Safety Agency for approval four months before the start of the second and subsequent emission trading periods;
* surrender each year to the registry referred to in Section 15 a number of emission allowances equal to the total aviation emissions produced during the previous calendar year; (37/2015)
* submit the information necessary for the application of free aviation emission allowances to the Finnish Transport Safety Agency; and
* inform the Finnish Transport Safety Agency of any changes in the operations or in emissions monitoring, and of any change of aircraft operator.

Anyone who, deliberately or through gross negligence,
* fails to draw up a monitoring plan as referred to in section 4 and have it approved by the Finnish Transport Safety Agency, or neglects the report or verification referred to in section 4;
* provides false information to the authority;
* uses an emission reduction or emission reduction unit contrary to section 14; or
* fails to present the documents and records referred to in section 21 (2),

If an aircraft operator fails to comply with the requirements of this Act and if the measures in sections 22-24 above have not been sufficient to ensure compliance, the Finnish Transport Safety Agency may request the European Commission to decide on the imposition of an operating ban on the aircraft operator concerned. Any request by the Finnish Transport Safety Agency shall include:
* evidence that the aircraft operator has not complied with its obligations under this Act;
* details of the enforcement action taken by the Agency;
* a justification for the imposition of an operating ban within the European Economic Area; and
* a recommendation for the scope of an operating ban within the European Economic Area and any conditions that should be applied.
